 period of\nP=0.5607222(2) d. The distance to the system is estimated to be\nd=135.2^{+7.6}_{-7.9} pc, in excellent agreement with the value from Gaia. If\nsolar metallicity were assumed, the age of the system would be older than\nlog(age)~8 based on the Mbol-log Teff diagram. NSVS 10653195 is composed of two\noversized and active K stars. While their radii is above model predictions\ntheir Teff are in better agreement with models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Jun 2019 16:28:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-17"}
