, surviving satellites are\nrelatively more massive, but tend to infall later into the host galaxy, thus\nreducing the time they are subjected to destructive environmental mechanisms\nand dynamical friction. In summary, our results suggest that the\ncharacteristics of satellites are mainly determined by their ability to\nefficiently cool gas that is accreted in the redshift range z=3-5, prior to\ntheir infall into the host galaxy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 19 Jun 2019 18:00:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-04"}
